    • Enum Constant Detail

      • OFF

        public static final ECachingStrategy OFF
        Performs no caching at all.

      • SINGLE

        public static final ECachingStrategy SINGLE
        Caches exactly one element (basically the same as an LRU cache with size 1.

      • LRU

        public static final ECachingStrategy LRU
        Last recently used caching strategy. The parameter denotes the maximal number of elements stored.

      • MEMORY

        public static final ECachingStrategy MEMORY
        Memory sensitive caching using SoftReferences. This allows the cache to keep elements as long as memory is available, but free memory when requested by the garbage collector.

      • UNLIMITED

        public static final ECachingStrategy UNLIMITED
        Unlimited caching, i.e. the cache never discard data. This can lead to situations where the memory is exceeded.
